Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.00,0:00:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,500 years ago, trans-oceanic travel became a reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.00,0:00:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Since the end of the last Ice Age,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.00,0:00:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,farming societies have been absorbing their neighbors,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.00,0:00:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,making populations more similar within continents.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.00,0:00:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That when people began to cross oceans, in large numbers,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.00,0:00:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the genetic and cultural differences between people from different continents
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.00,0:00:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,also began to fade, though not disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.00,0:00:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Many families relocated
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.00,0:00:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Willingly, or unwillingly
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.00,0:00:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to very distant lands.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.00,0:01:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes, they found unoccupied lands,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.00,0:01:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and sometimes they found lands occupied,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.00,0:01:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and wished they weren't.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.00,0:01:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And sometimes they found land and labor,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.00,0:01:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and devised ways of exploiting both.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.00,0:01:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All over the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.00,0:01:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,people separated by thousands of kilometers
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.00,0:01:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,for thousands of years began meeting once again and producing children.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.00,0:01:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, whole regions, like the Americas,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.00,0:01:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,are populated by people
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.00,0:01:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,who can trace their ancestry back to multiple continents.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.00,0:01:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But some small groups
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.00,0:01:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,are more geographically or culturally isolated,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.00,0:02:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and remain genetically distinguishable.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.00,0:02:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,As long distance transportation gets easier and easier,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.00,0:02:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and individual societies become more diverse,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.00,0:02:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,languages are being lost,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.00,0:02:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and genetic distinctions across the globe are fading.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.00,0:02:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But these genetic distinctions,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.00,0:02:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,are a relatively recent phenomenon in our history.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.00,0:02:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We haven't been separated for very long.
